Order should be respected, because further features depends to nearest ones (in the list of course).
- Verify the opcode has enough operands to work properly
- Pointers feature
- Labels to jmp
- Segments (constants, etc...)
- STRINGS (very needful), by putting them into constants segment and loading them from pointers.
- More opcodes
- Some memory zones to interact with things like stdout, stdin, etc...

BIGGEST GOAL: MAKE LAMP A 64-bit VIRTUAL MACHINE (32 is good too)